AN  - 612791363
ID  - 27477594 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=27477594]
T1  - Long-Term Use and Safety of Migraine Preventive Medications
A1  - VanderPluym J.
A1  - Evans R.W.
A1  - Starling A.J. 
Y1  - 2016//
N2  - Migraine preventive medications are used to reduce the frequency, severity, and disability of migraine attacks. Once migraine preventive therapy is initiated, the question of how long to maintain this therapy arises. This article will explore the literature pertaining to the long-term use of migraine preventive medications, including length of treatment and safety with long-term exposure.Copyright © 2016 American Headache Society
